cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper is primarily focused on network applications and the implementation of heavy hitter detection in the data-plane using programmable languages such as P4. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the challenges of implementing heavy hitter detection in programmable hardware, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes memory- and processing-efficient solutions, which could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
